        <paragraph>A node used to create a parallax scrolling background.</paragraph>
        <section classes="classref-introduction-group" ids="description" names="description">
            <title>Description</title>
            <paragraph>A ParallaxBackground uses one or more <reference internal="True" refuri="class_parallaxlayer#class-parallaxlayer"><inline classes="std std-ref">ParallaxLayer</inline></reference> child nodes to create a parallax effect. Each <reference internal="True" refuri="class_parallaxlayer#class-parallaxlayer"><inline classes="std std-ref">ParallaxLayer</inline></reference> can move at a different speed using <reference internal="True" refuri="class_parallaxlayer#class-parallaxlayer-property-motion-offset"><inline classes="std std-ref">ParallaxLayer.motion_offset</inline></reference>. This creates an illusion of depth in a 2D game. If not used with a <reference internal="True" refuri="class_camera2d#class-camera2d"><inline classes="std std-ref">Camera2D</inline></reference>, you must manually calculate the <reference internal="True" refid="class-parallaxbackground-property-scroll-offset"><inline classes="std std-ref">scroll_offset</inline></reference>.</paragraph>
            <paragraph><strong>Note:</strong> Each <strong>ParallaxBackground</strong> is drawn on one specific <reference internal="True" refuri="class_viewport#class-viewport"><inline classes="std std-ref">Viewport</inline></reference> and cannot be shared between multiple <reference internal="True" refuri="class_viewport#class-viewport"><inline classes="std std-ref">Viewport</inline></reference>s, see <reference internal="True" refuri="class_canvaslayer#class-canvaslayer-property-custom-viewport"><inline classes="std std-ref">CanvasLayer.custom_viewport</inline></reference>. When using multiple <reference internal="True" refuri="class_viewport#class-viewport"><inline classes="std std-ref">Viewport</inline></reference>s, for example in a split-screen game, you need create an individual <strong>ParallaxBackground</strong> for each <reference internal="True" refuri="class_viewport#class-viewport"><inline classes="std std-ref">Viewport</inline></reference> you want it to be drawn on.</paragraph>
